  "note": "2026-07-18 09:5x BST scheduled run (window after:2026/07/17). Filed 8 notes from 8 self-sent emails: 6 YouTube notes to YouTube-Queue, 1 text/body note (George Invoice (Intuit)) and 1 PDF attachment note (Payment Confirmation - Harry (Accountancy Fees)) to the inbox root. The Harry email body was signature-only so no body note; only the attachment note was created. The 'George invoice' email (subject was a .pdf filename) had NO real Gmail attachment - only a browser blob reference and an Intuit connect link - so it was filed as a text note capturing that link, no attachment fetch needed. No email produced 2+ notes, so no sibling cross-linking. Attachment used the Chrome 'Add to Drive' hop + Drive connector; download_file_content exceeded the token cap and auto-saved to a tool-result file, so decode_attachment.py --from-json decoded from that file (byte-exact 141,893 bytes, valid PDF v1.4, 1 page). pandoc cannot read PDF, so text was extracted with pdftotext -layout and hand-written into the note; the original PDF is kept in attachments/ and wikilinked. 8 threads labelled MCSB-Filed (Label_534) and archived. Skipped and logged (no note, not labelled, left in inbox): 7 auto-generated digests (4 US Active 10 news digests, 1 US correction email, 2 LSE RNS checks). NBLM directives applied by hand (extractor topic heuristic still weak, as flagged before): products=selling workshops, tldraw=tldraw, cowork=Cowork; the 'AI News' email was a false-positive NBLM (Mick describing the video, not a directive) so no action set.",
